                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>B. M. Kaplan.<lb/>
                736 Lexington Ave<lb/>
                New York<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. Sabato Morais.<lb/>
                546 N. Fifth St.<lb/>
                Philadelphia.<lb/>
                Pa.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>736 Lexington Av.&#44;<lb/>
                New York. Aug. 22&#44; 1897.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
                President of the Faculty of<lb/> the Jewish Theological Seminary&#59;<lb/>
                Esteemed Sir&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>Inasmuch as we are<lb/> college graduates and inasmuch<lb/> as the trustees&#44; thinking us capable<lb/> of assuming the functions of a<lb/> minister&#44; would be very pleased to<lb/> see us graduate from the Seminary&#44;<lb/> we&#44; the undersigned&#44; respectfully submit<lb/> to your kind and earnest consideration<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>the following&#58;&#45; We have already<lb/> fulfilled the general requirements<lb/> laid down in the curriculum of the<lb/> Seminary&#44; but we should like to<lb/> be posted especially on the techni&#45;<lb/>calities immediately connected with<lb/> the Rabbinical office&#44; such as the<lb/> Laws of Terephoth&#44; Kiddushin&#44; etc.<lb/>  We requested Dr. Joff&#233;&#44; our instructor<lb/> in Talmud&#44; to be kind enough to<lb/> form a graduating class where<lb/> the above named subjects should<lb/> be made a special study of&#44; so<lb/> as to give us an opportunity to<lb/> prepare ourselves to pass the exam&#45;<lb/>ination for the Rabbinical degree<lb/> creditably.  Dr. Joff&#233; referred us<lb/> to you&#44; saying that if you kindly<lb/> communicate with him&#44; he will be<lb/> pleased to form a graduating class<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>of us.<lb/></p>
            <p>Hoping that the matter<lb/> will receive your immediate<lb/> attention&#44; and awaiting your<lb/> kind reply&#44; we remain<lb/> Yours most respectfully&#44;<lb/> Morris Mandel.<lb/> Bernard M. Kaplan.<lb/>
                736 Lexington Av.&#44; N. Y. C.<lb/></p>
            <p>To the Rev. Dr. Sabato Morais&#44;<lb/> 546 North Fifth St.&#44; Phil.&#44; Pa.<lb/></p>
            </body>
